00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:20.479
it'll do the task of division. And so we get a vector that has, at the end, just as many values

00:12:20.479 --> 00:12:26.239
as the original vectors. Now this is great if you put your data in such a way that each variable is

00:12:26.239 --> 00:12:31.280
in its own column, and then each row contains a single observation. Because what element-wise

00:12:31.280 --> 00:12:36.479
operations will do is it'll make sure that the values of one observation are only paired with

00:12:36.479 --> 00:12:41.280
other values from the same observation, which as a data scientist is just what you want.

